The National Working Committee (NWC), on Tuesday, said it has dissolved the leadership of the Kano State chapter of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Hon. Umar M. Bature, National Organizing Secretary of the party in a statement on Tuesday, said after careful deliberations and extensive consultations, on behalf of the National Executive Committee (NEC), pursuant to Sections 29(2)(b) and 31(2)(e ), it dissolved the State, Local Government and Ward Executive Committees with immediate effect. Following the development, it said the NWC has approved the appointment of the Kano State Caretaker Committee to run the affairs of the party in the state for a period of 90 days from today, March 29, 2022, Pursuant to Section 24(2) of the party’s constitution as amended in 2017. It named the membership of the Kano State Caretaker are as; Alhaji Ibrahim Atta — Chairman, Alhaji Ibrahim Aminu Dan’Iya — Member, Hajiya Ladidi Dangalan — Member, Hon. Aminu Abdullahi Jungau — Member, Mukhtar Mustapha Janguza — Member, Abdullahi Isa Sulaiman — Member, Barr. Baba Lawan — Member/Secretary.